definition: Belgium/Belgian/abbr. for 比利時|比利时[Bi3 li4 shi2]
to compare/(followed by a noun and adjective) more {adj.} than {noun}/ratio/to gesture/(Taiwan pr. [bi4] in some compounds derived from Classical Chinese)
to come/to arrive/to come round/ever since/next

sentences.english: We last saw the boy playing nearby the river bank.
sentences.chinese: 本人们比来还看到阿谁小男孩在河滨玩。

sentences.english: On a hot day there's nothing I like more than a cold orange juice.
sentences.chinese: 我觉得，大热天没有比来杯橘子汁更过瘾的了。

sentences.english: And, for that, we use the Jacobian.
We can therefore, flexibly change the spectrum resolution by changing the decimation factor.
sentences.chinese: 可以灵活地改变选抽比来改变谱的分辨率。

sentences.english: 'I can't say I'm more  optimistic than I was before coming here,' Mr. Juncker added later.
sentences.chinese: 容克后来又说，我不能说我比来这里之前更加乐观了。

sentences.english: Why do critics insist on comparing one artist with another?
sentences.chinese: 为什么评论家们总是把艺术家们比来比去？

definition: (literary) every year/year after year/in recent years/Taiwan pr. [bi4 nian2]
lit. to have no time for civilities (idiom)/fig. not to be outdone/not to yield to one's opponents
at one's convenience/when one has time
to hurry/to rush/to run quickly/to elope
variant of 奔[ben1]/variant of 奔[ben4]
not at all the same/substantially different
